                    "kind": "text",
                    "data": "Pretty close, but not fully. Here's what I have solid vs. what's still opaque:\n\n**Well understood:**\n- All custom RTL (motor_controller hierarchy, watchdog, PWM, quadrature decoder)\n- Pin assignments and motor/encoder topology from the XDC\n- The block diagram IP inventory (from the directory listing of IP instances)\n\n**Not yet read:**\n- `Kria_BD.bd` — the actual block diagram source (170KB of JSON/TCL). This would tell me exact AXI address map, how each motor controller is wired to which AXI GPIO, interrupt routing, and clock configuration details.\n- The individual IP config files inside each `ip/` subdirectory — these would confirm parameter settings (e.g., GPIO widths, IIC clock speed, interrupt priorities)\n\nThe `.bd` file is the biggest gap. Without it I'm inferring the connectivity from the IP instance names alone. If you want a complete picture — like \"which AXI address does motor 7's control register live at\" — I'd need to read that file. Want me to dig into it?"
